headline: Google remedy proposals leave little room for settlement, says Wells Fargo
summary: Wells Fargo notes that Google filed a court filing and company blog detailing its proposed remedies in the Department of Justice search case. The firm believes Google’s proposals leave little room for negotiation of a settlement with the DOJ and likely ensure an appeal and resolution in 2-3 years. The overhang will remain but Wells sees no court-mandated meaningful changes to distribution relationships near term. The firm has an Equal Weight rating on the shares with a price target of $187. headline: Nvidia Stock Investors Just Got Bad News From AI Semiconductor Rival Broadcom
summary: Complex data center workloads like training machine learning models and running artificial intelligence (AI) applications would take a very long time if powered only by central processing units (CPUs).  In that semiconductor vertical, Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA) graphics processing units (GPUs) have emerged as the industry standard.  In fact, the company has between 80% and 95% market share in AI accelerators, according to analysts.
